Students take center stage at Zhejiang University's academic conference; research findings are mind-blowing - Xinhua News Agency
Using air to wash hands, diagnosing diseases with a breath, and accurately locating the source of smog were among the innovative academic achievements recognized at the opening ceremony of Zhejiang University's 2016 Academic Annual Meeting last night.
The main researchers behind these achievements are all students, and their research covers a wide range of fields, including environment, machinery, energy, medicine, life sciences, and humanities education. Starting from a curious idea, the students have created many high-end inventions with practical applications, some of which have won awards both domestically and internationally.
Biosensors: Your Family Health Check Doctor
Zhang Diming's team, doctoral students from the School of Biomedical Engineering, demonstrated a biosensor on a smartphone that is only half the size of a smartphone.
"You only need to exhale gently, and this device can perform a preliminary assessment of your health status from the composition of your exhaled breath."
Zhang Diming explained that this sensor system is connected to a smartphone, and a health report will be displayed on the phone after exhaling air.
Smart bracelets on the market that can detect health status generally detect physical parameters such as temperature and pulse.
This biosensor utilizes graphene, a novel material, which targets chemical elements. Its keen "sense of smell" allows it to more deeply and accurately reflect the body's health status.
Intelligent Surgical Lights: The Doctor's High-Energy Eyes
In addition to smartphones, smart surgical lights are now being used in operating rooms.
This invention won a silver medal at the 44th Geneva International Invention Exhibition in Switzerland this year.
The team of Zhu Linjing and Shen Junfei, master's students from the School of Optoelectronic Science and Engineering, explored new ideas based on the shortcomings of traditional surgical lights and invented the intelligent LED surgical shadowless light.
"Many diseases are not detected or removed in their early stages because of the lights used by doctors in the operating room."
Shen Junfei said that, for example, if doctors cannot see all the tumor tissue in time during early cancer screening, the cancer cells will spread later.
This intelligent surgical light has four light panels that can enhance the differentiation of different tissues under illumination by adjusting the spectrum.
During the procedure, doctors can adjust the size of the light spot, brightness, spectrum, color uniformity, and shadowlessness rate at any time according to the needs of the surgery and their personal habits.
This intelligent surgical light has been tested in hospitals such as Sir Run Run Shaw Hospital affiliated with Zhejiang University School of Medicine and Children's Hospital affiliated with Zhejiang University School of Medicine, and has received positive feedback.
Last October, this invention won the first prize in the National Challenge Cup.
Wash your hands with air: water-saving and cool.
Ordinary people wash their hands by rinsing with water, or at most by applying some soap and hand sanitizer. But Li Qizhang and his classmates invented an "air handwashing device".
Simply by standing on the handwashing station of the device, our weight can compress air out.
"It's like an air pump."
The compressed air forms a fluid at the tap and combines with the water.
That way, we can wash our hands clean!
Colorimetric reaction and bacterial residue tests have shown that the effect of washing hands in this way is the same as that of ordinary handwashing methods.
This device only relies on our own gravity as a driving force, which can ensure the cleaning effect while saving 90% of the water. The whole process is completely energy-free, making it energy-saving and environmentally friendly.
Last year, at the second Global Major Challenges Summit, this invention stood out among many of the world's top universities and won the only gold medal.
