A certificate I find very meaningful – First Aid Certificate
This is one of the skill certificates that I consider important, besides my driver's license!
Just to clarify: First aid measures are emergency rescue measures taken when a sudden incident occurs, that is, rescue before the ambulance arrives.
As we all know, there is a period of time between the arrival of the ambulance after an accident, and this period is the most critical.
This is when emergency medical assistance is needed.
If I were to suffer a heart attack, stroke, or respiratory arrest, the window of opportunity for survival would be only four minutes—the golden four minutes!
That's why it's so important for people around you to know first aid!
When someone around us collapses, we can use our professional knowledge to help them, instead of just standing there helplessly, unable to do anything. That feeling of helplessness is terrifying.
"In China, according to official data, three million people die from accidents every year, the most dangerous of which is cardiac arrest."
In the United States, on average, 15% of patients can be saved.
In Las Vegas casino hotels, 70-80% of businesses can be saved; in Shanghai and Beijing, the figure is less than 1%.
This was said by Lu Le, the founder of First Response.
If a person experiences cardiac arrest, stops breathing, and stops having a heartbeat, pinching the philtrum will have no effect.
Artificial respiration and chest compressions are necessary to save the person.
I've noticed that very few people are aware of the importance of learning first aid, but when something happens, it's often too late. So I urge everyone to learn this skill so that we can react promptly in emergencies.
It might even save someone's life!
You can register for a first aid certificate at your local Red Cross training center. I registered at the Red Cross training center in Zhuhai, and students get a discount.
P.S.: The last picture is a record of the goals I wanted to achieve before I turned 25. I added the first aid certificate to my list of goals a few months ago, but I did achieve it!
Next, I'm going to take other certification exams that I want to take. I plan to get a diving certification. I saw on Xiaohongshu that there's also a diving first aid certification. It seems that you need a first aid certification to take this exam, so a first aid certification is actually quite useful!
