Introduction to Zhengzhou Manhole Concrete Module Production and Processing Equipment:
Zhengzhou Yixin is a professional manufacturer of concrete inspection well modular brick making equipment, inspection well block machinery, and well wall module machinery in China, ranging from semi-automatic to fully automated production lines.
Through years of practice and development, we now possess high-quality equipment and mainly produce hydraulic, mobile, and fully automated inspection well series equipment and supporting devices.
Inspection well concrete module production and processing equipment assembly site in Zhengzhou:
Features and advantages of Zhengzhou manhole concrete module production and processing equipment:
Yixin inspection well block brick making equipment is a new type of masonry material widely applicable to municipal underground structures such as coal, heat, water, electricity, and gas.
Examples include various inspection wells, rainwater inlets, square ditches, septic tanks, and small structures such as bridge wing walls for drainage and water storage facilities.
The advantage of using concrete modules to build inspection wells is that the modules have a grooved structure on all four sides, which can be combined and masonry to form a chain.
The shear resistance of the well wall is far superior to that of the flat friction masonry.
The modules have a hollow structure. After being assembled and masonry, the longitudinal holes are interconnected and the transverse holes are intersecting. After the core is poured, a cast-in-place concrete mesh structure is formed, which plays a role in secondary reinforcement and waterproofing.
The module is equipped with reinforcing bar slots in both the longitudinal and transverse directions, and the transverse horizontal reinforcing bars and longitudinal reinforcing bars improve the overall strength of the structure.
In addition, inspection wells and drainage wells constructed using concrete inspection well modules are less prone to collapse, subsidence, and leakage. The well wall modules have stable mechanical properties, are easy to operate, and have standard forming dimensions.
The intelligent control system for concrete inspection well modular brick making equipment is equipped with data input and output devices, a one-button touch screen LCD display to monitor the entire mechanical operation process, and realizes ideal human-machine dialogue, automatic material comparison analysis, density operation, safety logic control, and fault diagnosis system.
The mechanical hydraulic system of the well wall module adopts single-cylinder hydraulic and conveying, and double-cylinder hydraulic and conveying.
An independent hydraulic integration station avoids the impact of host machine vibration on the hydraulic system, thus ensuring the reliability of the hydraulic system.
The concrete inspection well modular brick machine equipment features a material placing box, a moving mold box, demolding and rising, a material storage box door closing, and an automatic conveying pallet, all completed independently by a hydraulic system, thereby reducing mechanical wear and maintenance.
The concrete inspection well modular brick-making equipment adopts imported computers, electrical appliances, sealing components, and hydraulic components, ensuring the overall performance of the equipment is stable and reliable.
The mechanical vibration platform for the well wall module is made of integral steel plate, and the platform is cut by wire cutting and has no welding points, allowing the stuffing box to swing freely and guide, thus greatly reducing mechanical wear.
This reduces mold load and combines filling with a two-in-one, high-amplitude vibration system, employing integrated, fully synchronous table vibration and mold vibration to ensure effective compaction.
The well wall module uses mechanical excitation and computer-controlled automatic vibration amplitude adjustment based on the cost-effectiveness of raw materials, with wear-free braking, thereby extending service life and reducing costs.
The well wall module has both automatic and manual control functions.
