Chongqing vocational schools pilot modern apprenticeship system, students are considered prospective employees upon enrollment - Xinhua News Agency
Yesterday, reporters learned from the Municipal Education Commission that starting this year, the city will pilot the "modern apprenticeship" talent training model in 60 secondary vocational schools. Students who receive pilot training will also have apprentice status and will be pre-employed as employees by the pilot companies after enrollment.
The Municipal Education Commission requires that the enrollment and admission procedures of secondary vocational schools and the employment procedures of enterprises be standardized, and that the dual status of apprentices as students of secondary vocational schools and prospective employees of enterprises be clarified. In accordance with the principle of mutual selection, apprentices, schools and enterprises should sign a tripartite agreement. For apprentices who are 16 years of age or older but under 18 years of age, a four-party agreement should be signed by the apprentice, guardian, school and enterprise to determine the rights and interests of all parties and the specific positions, teaching content and rights protection of apprentices in on-the-job training.
Pilot schools are encouraged to adopt the modern apprenticeship system to jointly conduct pre-job training and job transfer training for enterprise employees with partner companies.
Pilot schools should reform their talent cultivation models.
The school and enterprises jointly design talent training programs and jointly formulate professional teaching standards, curriculum standards, job standards, enterprise mentor standards, quality monitoring standards, and corresponding implementation plans.
The pilot program uses the length of the academic program as a pilot cycle. The internship period for students in enterprises is determined according to the professional talent training program, and the on-the-job internship is generally 6 months.
In practice, a team-based management model should be implemented in enterprises. Depending on the characteristics of different majors, one mentor can lead 2 to 5 apprentices to form a learning group, ensuring that students master the skills required for each training position.
According to the plan, from 2016 to August 2019, our city selected 60 municipal-level pilot projects for the modern apprenticeship system in secondary vocational schools in three batches, with each pilot project having about 50 students, training a total of about 3,000 students (apprentices).
Following the principle of piloting first and then promoting, and gradually expanding from specific points to a wider area, we will explore and establish a long-term mechanism for joint enrollment, joint training, and integrated education between schools and enterprises, so as to effectively improve students' job skills and increase their employment rate and quality.
