The China National Children's Center will hold a series of activities to let children celebrate Children's Day with "high technology" - Xinhua News Agency
BEIJING, May 20 (Xinhua) -- The China National Children's Center plans to hold a series of activities from May 28 to June 1, around Children's Day, including children's maker experiences, a children's visual arts festival, and a parent-child book carnival, to allow children to spend Children's Day surrounded by the charm of cutting-edge technology, according to the center on May 20.
It is understood that the activities held by the China National Children's Center during this year's Children's Day include the "Love Home, Create Cool" Children's Future Learning Carnival, the first Children's Visual Arts Festival, the "Book Carnival" event, and the "Family Loves Reading" picture book series activities.
Li Zhongming, deputy director of the China National Children's Center, introduced at a media briefing held on June 20th for Children's Day 2016 that the "Love Home, Create Cool" Children's Future Learning Carnival is a key event of the China National Children's Center's celebration of Children's Day this year.
The event aims to organically combine social innovation with individual family creativity, and through children and families participating in various innovative educational activities, make innovative practices a cultural gene of families, and make "hands-on" a new learning and lifestyle for families.
It is reported that the "Love Home, Create Cool" Children's Future Learning Carnival includes dozens of cutting-edge technology experience activities such as the "Douguo Maker" experience activities, the anniversary celebration of Lao Niu Children's Exploration Hall and the "Explore the Whole Family, Love Children, and Celebrate Children's Day" event, the VR All-People Experience Program, and the "Maker Tribe" interactive workshop.
