Jiangxi to train 10,000 rural primary school music, physical education, and art teachers within three years - Xinhua News Agency
NANCHANG, May 22 (Xinhua) -- According to the Jiangxi Provincial Department of Education, in order to enhance the capacity to support teachers in shortage subjects and achieve balanced development of compulsory education in rural areas, Jiangxi Province plans to train one qualified music, art, and physical education teacher for each primary school in rural areas (townships and below) throughout the province over three years, starting in 2016, for a total of 10,000 teachers.
It is understood that the training is for primary school teachers under the age of 45 in rural areas of Jiangxi Province who have basic knowledge or talent in music, art, and physical education and can also teach other subjects such as music, art, and physical education.
Through training, they will acquire basic knowledge and teaching skills in music, physical education, and art, update their teaching ideas and concepts, master modern teaching methods, improve their subject teaching ability, activity design ability, campus culture ability, and self-development ability, build a team of music, physical education, and art teachers with multiple skills, and alleviate the problem of shortage of music, physical education, and art teachers in rural areas.
To ensure the quality and effectiveness of the training, Jiangxi Province has also planned to train one teacher each in music, art, and physical education from 100 counties (cities and districts) across the province, for a total of 300 trainees. This will comprehensively improve their teaching demonstration and guidance abilities, teaching and research activity design and organization abilities, training abilities, and online training workshop construction abilities, so as to play the roles of teaching, demonstration, guidance, and supervision.
