Actually, there are many things to consider when it comes to dressing for slightly chubby girls.
For plus-size girls, skirts should not be too short or too long. The length should be around the knee, just enough to cover the thicker parts of the thighs.
A skirt that is too short will reveal the fat on your legs.
Too long a length can make someone appear short and stout.
If you wear clothes that divide the body into three sections—top, middle, and bottom—you will appear taller. This is achieved by using different colors for the top, skirt, and stockings, which will create a slender look.
In fact, many dark-colored clothes are a staple for slightly chubby girls (the author has personal experience with this). Dark colors are also a good way to hide your body's weight. A noble and elegant black short skirt is also the first choice for slightly chubby girls.
Wearing dark-colored clothes, especially a black short skirt, will make you look thinner.
If you have thick calves, avoid wearing socks and shoes that draw attention to them.
The more mainstream the better, and the colors shouldn't be too bright.
To avoid giving the impression of being overweight when people focus on your legs and feet.
For slightly chubby girls, it's essential to know the tricks of dressing well.
Slightly chubby girls should avoid wearing tight-fitting short skirts. Also, tops should not be too short or tucked into the skirt, as this will look uncomfortable. If you have thick legs, wear black stockings or fishnet stockings (the kind with fine checks). Choose a soft-textured printed flared skirt and pair it with a cowl-neck top, which can effectively conceal the flaws of a chubby girl.
Of course, there are also some things to keep in mind when slightly chubby girls wear short skirts.
Plus-size girls should choose a top that matches the color of the skirt when wearing a short skirt. This will make your plus-size figure appear taller.
A short skirt paired with high heels can make your legs look longer, which is the most fashionable combination for summer!
If you are a woman with a fuller upper body but slimmer legs, I recommend choosing a glamorous short dress.
Not only can it cover up your big belly, it can also show off your best features.
A-line skirts are very slimming and are more suitable for plus-size girls. Choose a tighter-fitting top to create a layered look that will make you appear even slimmer.
A simple white T-shirt paired with a short skirt is a great option even for plus-size women.
Slightly chubby girls can also create a fashionable look.
As long as you master the rules of dressing and matching, even slightly chubby girls can become the center of attention.
After making changes to my clothing style, I also need to exercise more in my daily life, hoping to shed the "slightly chubby girl" label as soon as possible! 😄
The 18th World Beverage Innovation Awards are an award jointly organized by FoodBev Media and Brau Beviale, the international trade fair for the beer, brewing and beverage industry in Nuremberg, Germany.
It attracted 279 entries from 25 countries and 22 different categories.
On October 15, the list of finalists was announced, and the final winners will be announced online on November 11 (British Summer Time).
We see that Genki Forest's LP28 sugar-free yogurt was shortlisted for the Best Dairy Beverage Award, Yili's "GOGO Wuhan" marketing campaign was shortlisted for Best Marketing Campaign, and Pepsi's packaging collaboration with People's Daily New Media was shortlisted for the Best Packaging Design/Label Award.
Laura Nettle, Senior Marketing Director at FoodBev Media, said: "We are delighted to celebrate the 18th annual World Beverage Innovation Awards with Brau Beviale."
From new flavors, concepts, and features to branding, packaging, and manufacturing, we are seeing trends in the beverage industry as it continues to innovate in a more sustainable way.
The World Beverage Innovation Awards recognize the most ambitious new products and developments from both established and emerging brands in the global beverage industry this year.
Below is the complete list of finalists for each category.
The technology developed by Ardagh Group can remelt 100% recycled glass into new bottles.
The water in the box is packaged in a 100% recyclable box, which reduces packaging by 66% and carbon emissions by 97%.
LatCub is 100% biodegradable, uses less paper, and does not use environmentally harmful glues or tapes.
The technology developed by Ardagh Group can remelt 100% recycled glass to make new bottles.
The final winners will be announced on November 11 (British Summer Time) on FoodBev Media's YouTube channel. FBIF will continue to provide coverage, so stay tuned!
