What was the hottest thing in 2021?
It is undoubtedly the Tokyo Olympics.
Do you think only Olympic athletes can win medals?
A while ago, an article titled "Look! Project Managers Can Compete for Olympic Gold Medals" went viral. It mentioned that project managers are absolutely unmatched in many projects: manual labor, business trips, and staying up all night are the daily routines of project managers, and putting out fires, taking the blame, and apologizing are all commonplace.
What appears to be a joking article actually reveals the daily hardships of project managers, reflecting their sense of powerlessness in the face of current project management challenges.
Those working in project management are also gradually choosing to take certain actions to get out of the predicaments in their work.
Judging from the increasing number of people registering for the PMP (Project Management Professional) certification each year, more and more project management professionals are improving their project management skills through learning.
According to the "China Project Management 20-Year Development Report (1999-2019)," as of September 2019, the cumulative number of PMP® applicants nationwide was nearly 600,000, the number of people who passed the PMP® certification was about 420,000, and the number of valid PMP® holders was about 300,000, accounting for 31.2% of the total number of PMP® holders worldwide.
The number of PMP certified individuals has been increasing year by year over the past 10 years, which shows that more and more project managers realize that it is no longer advisable to simply copy past "old experiences" to do things. The ever-changing work environment makes us realize that we must learn to stand on the shoulders of scientific giants to explore the way forward.
However, does passing the PMP exam guarantee smooth project management?
Many project management beginners say that by learning PMP/IPMP and other related courses, they can systematically master the knowledge points of the ten areas and five process groups of project management, but when they actually do project management work, they are still completely confused.
Many project managers frequently report the following problems: Inadequate understanding of project management, relying solely on personal experience, possessing project management theory but unsure how to put it into practice; lack of systematic project management processes and procedures, resulting in inaccurate project forecasts, poor control and sensitivity, and prolonged project delays; unclear division of responsibilities among team members, with experienced team members unsure how to handle cross-departmental collaboration and communication difficulties, hindering project progress…
Therefore, Zhongtian Huaxia Consulting, which has focused on product innovation and R&D management for more than a decade and has helped many outstanding companies cultivate a large number of key R&D talents such as product managers and project managers, and has won honors such as "China's Enterprise R&D Management Talent Training Demonstration Base", is here with the online course "R&D Project Manager Training Camp".
The "R&D Project Manager Training Camp" online course is a fragmented online learning method that combines numerous practical cases, tools, and methods from R&D companies to help you master the essential knowledge and standard procedures for project managers and embark on your own advanced project management journey.
This is also an opportunity for companies to accelerate the training of project managers with lower costs and less investment, thereby bringing efficient operational results to the company.
Seeing is believing, so let's see what other students are saying about this course: This course is not only taught by the Zhongtian Huaxia expert team (formerly Huawei's R&D management team), but also combines internationally advanced project management methodologies with real business scenarios from many well-known companies, providing in-depth yet easy-to-understand professional explanations of the course content.
Furthermore, it will provide scientific and practical management tools and methods, as well as a wealth of templates and forms, to help students apply what they have learned to their specific work after class.
