Home Credit advocates rational consumption ahead of "Double Twelve" - ​​Economic Observer Network - Professional Financial News Website
This year's "Double Eleven" shopping festival saw a record-breaking 1.77 trillion yuan in online payment transactions nationwide.
The wide variety of discount coupons and eye-catching live-streaming e-commerce have once again made consumers exclaim that they have benefited greatly. This consumption boom makes people marvel at the increasingly strong national consumption power, but on the other hand, it also makes people calmly consider the impact of consumerism on society and the contemporary mainstream consumer group.
On the eve of "Double Twelve," Home Credit Consumer Finance Co., Ltd. (hereinafter referred to as "Home Credit") issued a rational consumption advocacy, reminding users, especially young people, to establish good consumption awareness and habits, and to refuse blind and excessive consumption.
According to the "Consumer Financial Literacy Survey and Analysis Report" released by the People's Bank of China this year, the national consumer financial literacy index is 66.81, an increase of 2.04 compared with 2019.
Overall, Chinese residents have performed well in terms of financial consumption, but there are significant differences in their financial behavior and skills, and there is still a need to further improve their basic financial literacy.
The financial literacy levels of the elderly and teenagers are relatively low, and these two groups will remain key targets for continued financial education. Nielsen's "Report on the Debt Status of Young People in China" and CCTV Finance's "2019-2020 China Youth Consumption Report" show that the younger generation has enormous consumption potential, with credit consumption becoming an important way to upgrade consumption. 86.6% of young people use credit products, and nearly half have no accumulated debt. While the younger generation generally exhibits a rational consumption trend, which is quite different from the "excessive spending" label attached to them, some young people do indeed engage in excessive consumption and trend-following consumption behaviors, resulting in excessive financial pressure and debt risks, and even leading to a gradual increase in social problems. Financial institutions should bravely shoulder social responsibility and provide positive guidance.
As a licensed consumer finance institution, Home Credit has always been committed to helping people build their happy lives with high-quality and considerate services, advocating that consumers establish sound and correct consumption values, and actively responding to regulatory calls to enhance the rational consumption awareness of consumers, especially young people, through practical actions.
Over the years, Home Credit has been conducting comprehensive and diversified financial literacy campaigns for young people, including college students. Through collaborations with top domestic universities and innovation practice competitions, it has subtly guided the consumption needs of young people, helping them establish rational consumption concepts, plan their consumption needs reasonably, and ultimately help them accumulate wealth.
As Double Twelve approaches, Home Credit reminds all consumers to cultivate a rational consumption mindset and a correct view of money, resist blind and excessive consumption, and avoid common pitfalls in consumer lending to prevent impacting their personal credit and future economic life.
When making purchases, be sure to plan ahead, spend within your means, and repay on time.
If the payment is overdue, the overdue record will be recorded in your personal credit report, which may have an adverse impact on your future economic life, such as buying a car or a house.
At the same time, when enjoying financial products and services, one should choose formal institutions and channels, and pay attention to verifying whether the relevant institutions have the necessary operating qualifications.
In the future, Home Credit will continue to leverage its mature and reliable consumer finance system and constantly updated financial products to bring consumers more tailored and diversified services, continuously help the public improve their financial literacy, help consumers cultivate the concept of rational consumption and moderate borrowing, and become a consumer finance partner that consumers can trust for life.
