It's known as having the loudest exhaust noise from a supercar in the new district!
The car our team is bringing you this time is the dream car of many men!
It is Lamborghini's flagship supercar, the successor to the Murcielago—the Aventador LP700-4!
The asking price is nearly two million Malaysian Ringgit, and the annual road tax is over ten thousand Malaysian Ringgit. It's a four-wheel drive vehicle, so why is it called LP700?
With 700 horsepower, can you imagine how fast it is?
Well, never mind, I don't know either. The data says it only takes 2.9 seconds to accelerate from 0-100km/h, which means my Myvi is only about 30km/h while the other car is already at 100km/h.
The low-slung body, the imposing scissor doors, the massive air intakes all around the car, and the 6.5 V12 engine visible through the glass perfectly embody the Lamborghini style.
There's not much to say about the car models; just Google it yourself. I've compiled some explanations that Google might not provide!
Being in the spotlight so much, everyone's watching me wherever I go, it's really uncomfortable! (Actually, it's kind of fun.)
The fuel cost is around RM1 per kilometer (which the car owner doesn't care about at all).
You need to practice getting on and off the vehicle, otherwise it might be a bit awkward (because you might not be able to climb out of the vehicle and get stuck halfway).
The engine was so loud that you'd experience temporary deafness after getting out of the car. (But it was still a lot of fun!)
The car is too big, and it will be very narrow in a regular parking space. I'm afraid it will hit the door of the car next to me when it opens!
It's a bit lonely because there are no competitors on the road (this is just my opinion, it has nothing to do with the car owner, haha).
