Let the spirit of universities resonate with the spirit of the times - Xinhua Net
The so-called university spirit refers to a series of educational philosophies and values ​​that a university has accumulated over a long period of time in its development process; it is the soul of the university.
Throughout history, the spirit of the university has been crucial to the development of politics, economy, culture, science and technology, society, and even the progress of a nation.
Since the birth of the world's first modern university, universities have shouldered a unique mission that is different from other social organizations. For Chinese universities, which arose during a time of national crisis, their spirit is deeply influenced by traditional culture and the changes of the times, advocating the values ​​of "cultivating virtue and benefiting the world, and governing the country and bringing peace to the world" and the patriotic responsibility of "strengthening the country through education".
Currently, the trends of informatization and internationalization in higher education are becoming increasingly apparent, and global competition in education, technology, and talent is intensifying. As an important "supply side," higher education is facing unprecedented opportunities and challenges in its structural reforms.
In particular, the "Overall Plan for Coordinating the Development of World-Class Universities and Disciplines" not only demonstrates my country's confidence and determination to move from a large country in higher education to a strong country in higher education, but also sets higher and newer requirements for university development.
How can we strive to join the ranks of the world's top universities in a relatively short period of time, and accelerate the construction of several world-class universities and a number of world-class disciplines while still having a certain gap, so as to achieve a "leapfrog development"?
In addition to maintaining confidence in their goals, pathways, and capabilities, universities should fully leverage three advantages: First, the advantage of being a latecomer, by continuously attracting outstanding overseas academic talent and learning from the advanced experiences of world-class universities to significantly improve their academic level and educational quality; second, the advantage of culture, by inheriting the wisdom accumulated over five thousand years of Chinese civilization and promoting and developing excellent traditional culture to unite forces, build brands, and enhance their image; and third, the advantage of the system, by leveraging the superiority of the socialist system, strengthening goal-driven development, building consensus and synergy, and optimizing resource allocation to provide a sustainable and solid guarantee for universities to accelerate their catch-up with world-class standards.
It is particularly important to realize that building world-class universities cannot be done in the same way. While leveraging their strengths, each university must highlight its individuality and characteristics.
The distinctive features of schools should not only have common Chinese characteristics, but also reflect their unique goals, traditions, and resource endowments.
For Zhejiang University, we emphasize three distinctive features in our education: First, we highlight the cultivation of innovative and entrepreneurial talents, build an integrated educational environment that combines science and education with industry-university collaboration, and form a full-chain entrepreneurial education ecosystem; second, we emphasize the convergence of interdisciplinary disciplines, promote the optimization and adjustment of the disciplinary system, create an institutional environment for interdisciplinary collaboration, and actively cultivate emerging interdisciplinary disciplines and landmark interdisciplinary achievements; third, we emphasize the characteristics of our educational system and social service, carry out in-depth international exchanges and cooperation, and accelerate the formation of a pan-Zhejiang University industry-university-research cooperation system.
In this process, it is especially important to always uphold the spirit of the university and ensure that the spirit of the university resonates with the spirit of the times.
For Zhejiang University, the motto "Seeking Truth and Innovation," the shared values ​​of "Diligent Study, Moral Cultivation, Discernment, and Steadfastness," and the principles of "Embracing the Ocean, Enlightening Truth and Cultivating Virtue, Pioneering and Leading the People, and Building Our Nation" together constitute the latest expression of the spirit of Zhejiang University.
This is an important guarantee for the school to adhere to the correct direction of education, continuously accumulate cultural depth, and unite spiritual strength. It has rich connotations and profound significance.
Among them, "Embracing the Seas and Rivers" emphasizes the spirit of openness and inclusiveness, embodying the ambition of "making the best talents in the world available to us," and demonstrating the absorption of the high-quality educational philosophies of world-renowned universities; "Enlightening Truth and Cultivating Virtue" emphasizes the spirit of seeking truth and goodness, referring to the fact that while pursuing truth, universities should also receive moral cultivation and character refinement; "Opening Up the World and Leading the People" embodies the spirit of reform and innovation, including the pursuit of new knowledge and scientific research, and also demonstrating reform and development, and innovation; "Building Our Nation" emphasizes the spirit of patriotism and dedication, speaking of how universities should always share the glory and disgrace of the nation.
This series of spiritual ideals and values ​​is the soul of Zhejiang University's 120 years of education.
"The wise hear what is unseen, and the insightful see what is yet to be seen."
Chinese universities should further base themselves on the overall situation of the cause of socialism with Chinese characteristics, deeply grasp the era's position and historical mission of higher education, and accelerate their development into world-class universities.
At the same time, we must uphold humanistic care and independence and freedom, allowing the spirit of the university to resonate with the spirit of the times and the spirit of the nation, thereby providing inexhaustible impetus for achieving national prosperity and rejuvenation and realizing the common ideals of mankind.
