Iranian President: Nuclear Deal Expected if Sanctions Against Iran Are Lifted - Xinhua News Agency
TEHRAN, Dec. 11 (Xinhua) -- Iranian President Raisi said in Tehran on Tuesday that a "good agreement" could be reached in negotiations on the Iran nuclear deal if the United States lifts sanctions against Iran.
According to a statement released on the Iranian presidential website, Raisi said during a meeting with Iranian ambassadors to neighboring countries that Iran has demonstrated its sincerity in negotiations by submitting proposals to other parties involved in the Iran nuclear deal.
If the US is determined, "the path to an agreement will be clear."
The parties involved in the Iran nuclear deal began talks in Vienna, the capital of Austria, in April this year to discuss the resumption of compliance between the United States and Iran.
The new round of talks began in Vienna on November 29, adjourned temporarily on December 3, and resumed on December 9.
