Xi Jinping sends congratulatory letter to the 2021 Greater Bay Area Science Forum - Xinhua News Agency
Xinhua News Agency, Beijing, December 11 -- On December 11, President Xi Jinping sent a congratulatory letter to the 2021 Greater Bay Area Science Forum.
Xi Jinping pointed out that the world today is undergoing profound changes unseen in a century, and global scientific and technological innovation is entering a period of intense activity. A new round of scientific and technological revolution and industrial transformation has had a profound impact on the global economic structure.
The Guangdong-Hong Kong-Macao Greater Bay Area should focus on its strategic positioning as an international science and technology innovation center, strive to build a global science and technology innovation hub, and promote the development of emerging industries.
China is willing to work with scientists from all over the world and international science and technology organizations to strengthen international scientific and technological exchanges and cooperation, enhance research on major scientific issues, promote solutions to common scientific and technological problems, deepen cooperation on key scientific projects, jointly advance the development of the world's scientific cause, and better benefit mankind.
The 2021 Greater Bay Area Science Forum opened in Guangzhou, Guangdong Province, on the same day. The theme was "Exploring the Future, Sharing Science". It was hosted by the People's Government of Guangdong Province.
