As NFTs rapidly gain popularity, a new concept has emerged in the crypto community.
In 2021, a blockchain game called Axie Infinity had a huge impact in Southeast Asia, with some residents who lost their jobs due to the pandemic starting to earn a stable income through the game.
Axie Infinity is a pet-raising game based on blockchain technology, which combines various gameplay elements including NFTs. It is currently the NFT project with the highest transaction volume, exceeding $3 billion to date.
According to TokenTerminal data, Axie Infinity's daily revenue exceeds $8.2 million, approaching that of "Honor of Kings".
On August 6th of this year, Axie Infinity officially announced that its daily active users had exceeded 1 million.
The popularity of Axie Infinity has brought a new "playtoearn" model to more people. With the help of blockchain and smart contracts, players are no longer just single characters. In addition to getting fun and economic benefits from the game, they can also participate in the governance of the game ecosystem.
This subjectivity is not granted by the game developers, but is guaranteed by blockchain technology.
Seeing a news report about a friend's stock price, my biggest takeaway is the importance of choosing the right industry for a company, which means choosing the right industry for investment. First, you should choose an industry with large growth potential, with a market size of at least 100 billion yuan. Second, you should choose an industry with good future growth prospects, considering industries whose growth will reach its peak in the next 3-5 years. Finally, you should choose an industry with policy support.
The width of the track refers to the market size, the length of the track refers to the stage of development of the industry, and whether the track is flat or rugged refers to the competitive landscape of the industry.
Go for the right track!
The first thing to do in the new year is to summarize 2021 and adjust the tactical layout for 2022.
The tactic is to "do the things right," that is, to do things correctly.
The strategy lies in "doing the right thing," which means doing the right thing.
Strategy is about finding direction, tactics are about implementation, and there is room for strategic thinking above most tactical thinking.
For example, beyond increasing customer numbers (tactical thinking), one can consider whether to deepen existing expertise or expand into newer areas (strategic thinking); beyond improving customer retention (tactical thinking), one can consider how to improve the retention rate of core and high-value customers (strategic thinking); beyond increasing activity engagement (tactical thinking), one can consider how to set the right activity KPIs to achieve the right activity goals, such as increasing the engagement of target customers, activating high-value dormant customers, and precisely acquiring new customers; beyond increasing DAU (tactical thinking), one can consider whether the current growth is healthy and sustainable.
Twelve years after its inception, Bitcoin reached several milestones in 2021.
On September 7, El Salvador, a small Central American country, recognized Bitcoin as legal tender, marking the first time Bitcoin has become a legal tender in a country or region.
On October 12, the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC) approved ProShares' Bitcoin ETF for the first time in eight years, which was then listed on the New York Stock Exchange. This marked the debut of the first compliant Bitcoin futures ETF on the U.S. capital market, further expanding cryptocurrency investment exposure.
From the perspective of blockchain technology development, Bitcoin is not the main player.
On November 14, 2021, Bitcoin underwent a soft fork upgrade called "Taproot". This upgrade improved the anonymity of Bitcoin network transactions and reduced the data burden in transactions by changing the data structure of the blocks themselves.
