Have you encountered any issues with continuing education hours for your initial Level 1 cost engineer registration?
Those who register overdue and fail to provide continuing education certificates should provide proof of at least 30 hours of continuing education within the past year for overdue registration. For re-registration, proof of at least 120 hours of continuing education within the past four years should be provided. For re-registration, proof of at least 30 hours of continuing education for each full year should also be provided.
Continuing Education Fee Standards for Cost Engineers
Cost engineers participating in online continuing education must pay tuition fees to the relevant management agency upon registration. The standard fee is generally 300 yuan per person per year for 30 hours of compulsory courses (including the unified continuing education textbooks).
The cost of a 30-hour elective course is 300 yuan per person per year.
The cost of 30 hours of compulsory courses and 30 hours of elective courses is 600 yuan per person per year (including the unified continuing education textbooks).
(a) Registered cost engineers who participate in online continuing education programs organized by the China Cost Engineering Association or provincial and departmental management agencies shall have their credit hours calculated based on the time recorded in the online learning materials;
(ii) Participation in centralized face-to-face training for registered cost engineers organized by the China Cost Engineering Association or provincial and departmental management agencies, as well as various types of training courses and seminars, can be recognized as 4 credit hours per half-day;
(iii) Participation in continuing education courses for cost engineers and cost estimators organized by the China Cost Engineering Association and various provincial and departmental organizations can be recognized as 10 credit hours per half-day;
(iv) Participation in research projects funded by the China Price Association and provincial-level projects, the development of industry standards, and the compilation of teaching materials will be recognized with 30 credit hours per year for each project.
(vi) Participation in the compilation of textbooks, question setting, review, and grading of the national cost engineer professional qualification examination can be recognized as 30 credit hours per year;
(vii) Professional papers and books related to engineering cost that are published in public under an individual's name (based on the official publication number).
12 credit hours are awarded for every 10,000 words of published works;
Publishing a paper in a national-level journal earns 8 credit hours per thousand words; publishing a paper in a provincial-level journal earns 5 credit hours per thousand words; and publishing a paper in a municipal-level journal earns 3 credit hours per thousand words.
(ix) Participation in open training programs (excluding general management and skills training) organized by engineering cost consulting firms approved or authorized by the China Engineering Cost Association, provincial and departmental management agencies, and provincial engineering cost associations can be recognized as 4 credit hours per half-day, with a maximum of 30 credit hours per year.
Online Continuing Education Learning Process for Cost Engineers
Once the registration agency receives the payment, the student's account will be activated, and the cost engineer can then access the online education classroom using their username and password.
Students learn through methods such as accessing courseware, asking and answering questions, and online discussions.
If you forget your password and encounter an error message indicating that your username and password are incorrect, and you are unable to log in to study, please contact your registration institution. The registration institution can assist in changing your password (but cannot change your username). Use the changed password to log in again.
