In September 2020, Mr. Lu learned about a factory in Zhangting Town, Yuyao, Zhejiang Province from a real estate agency. After viewing the property several times, Mr. Lu decided to buy it.
In December of the same year, after discussing the details of purchasing the factory building with Mr. Lin, a family member of the property owner, Mr. Lu transferred 200,000 yuan as a deposit through bank transfer on the same day.
Mr. Lin signed the "Receipt for Factory Building Purchase Deposit" as the recipient, which stated that "if the buyer does not want to buy this factory building, this deposit will belong to the seller. If the seller does not want to sell this factory building, the deposit will be returned to the seller in double. Both parties agree to sign the factory building purchase contract within one week."
However, the two parties failed to reach an agreement on key contract terms such as the scope of the factory sale and payment methods, which delayed the signing of the house sale contract.
Considering that the two parties failed to reach a consensus on the contract terms, a few days later, Mr. Lin returned the 200,000 yuan deposit to Mr. Lu.
Mr. Lu had finally found a house he liked, paid the deposit, and prepared the remaining balance. He was just one step away from signing the contract when the seller refused to sell, leaving him feeling helpless and angry.
Therefore, Mr. Lu filed a lawsuit against Mr. Lin in the Yuyao City People's Court.
After hearing the case, the court held that the failure of the two parties to sign a formal contract could not be solely attributed to the defendant. It should be reasonably presumed that the negotiations failed. Therefore, the penalty clause for deposits should not apply in this case, and the defendant is not liable for breach of contract by returning double the deposit.
After the initial judgment, the plaintiff filed an appeal.
Recently, the appellate court upheld the original verdict.
[Lawyer's Reminder] During the transaction process, it is essential to exercise due diligence.
When signing a contract, the buyer must exercise due diligence, such as verifying the information of the property owner, whether the property is occupied, and specifying the exact time and place of delivery in the contract to prevent disputes from arising during the performance of the contract.
(Deutsche Welle Chinese) Following the conclusion of the "Democracy Summit" on Friday, a spokesperson for the Chinese Foreign Ministry issued a statement on Saturday (December 11) stating that the United States' hosting of the "Leaders' Democracy Summit" was "drawing ideological lines, instrumentalizing and weaponizing democracy, using the name of democracy to carry out anti-democratic activities, inciting division and confrontation, and diverting domestic contradictions."
The Chinese government believes that "for a long time, the United States has imposed its own political system and values ​​on others, promoted 'democratic reforms,' abused unilateral sanctions, and instigated 'color revolutions,' causing disastrous consequences."
'Democracy' has long been used by the United States as a 'weapon of mass destruction' to interfere in other countries.
This summit is Biden's way of fulfilling his campaign promises.
The two-day meeting was held via video conference, with leaders from 111 countries invited to participate, including the leader of Taiwan, but China and Russia were not invited.
On the eve of the summit, China and Russia criticized the United States, citing problems with its own democracy, and said that the United States was not qualified to host such a summit.
There have been voices of doubt both internationally and within the United States. For example, some have criticized the fact that the invited participants included leaders with authoritarian tendencies, such as the leaders of the Philippines, Poland, and Brazil. Some have questioned whether the Biden administration's true intention in organizing the summit was not for democracy but for geopolitical purposes.
Newly appointed German Chancellor Olaf Scholz also participated in the video democracy summit.
A statement from the Chinese Foreign Ministry on Saturday said that "today's American democracy is showing its pathological side, with problems such as money politics, identity politics, partisan antagonism, political polarization, social division, racial conflict, and widening wealth gap becoming increasingly serious." The statement further claimed that American democracy is a "rich man's game" built on a foundation of capital.
In his speech, US President Biden stated, "As leaders of government, we have a responsibility to listen to our citizens, strengthen the safeguards of democracy, push for reform, achieve transparent and accountable governance, and better withstand the buffers and shocks of authoritarianism, as well as those who seek power nakedly above the public good."
He emphasized that democracy is not something to be taken for granted, "We must constantly update it in each generation, and in my view, this is the defining challenge of our time."
Biden also said that global democracy and human rights "face ongoing and worrying challenges, and democracy needs fighters to defend it."
The United States has pledged a year-long action following this democracy summit, including a $424.4 million initiative to strengthen democracy around the world and support independent news media.
The United States hopes that countries will make concrete public commitments to improve their democratic systems ahead of the physical democracy summit scheduled for the end of 2022.
Biden said, "Let's have all our countries fulfill our commitments and report on the progress we've made next year."
