Education News: Beijing Reduces the Proportion of Students with Special Talents for Junior High School Admissions in 2016 - Xinhua News Agency
On the 21st and 22nd, the examination for students with special talents for junior high school admission in Beijing was organized and implemented by the education commissions of each district.
This year, all districts in Beijing have reduced the proportion of students admitted based on their special talents, making the competition for these students even fiercer.
Taking Dongcheng District as an example, this year the proportion of students with special talents entering junior high school from primary school in the district will not exceed 5% of the district's total enrollment plan. The planned enrollment number is 380 students, and the proportion of students actually attending school will not exceed 10% of the school's enrollment plan.
Students with special talents in sports, arts, or science and technology who register online are eligible to participate in the special talent admission examination.
To facilitate students' participation in the assessments at nearby locations, Dongcheng District has continued last year's assessment arrangement, setting up 1-2 assessment locations in each school district, for a total of 13 assessment locations.
The test centers are divided into test rooms according to test areas, and time slots are divided by hour. On the day of the test, students will enter the test center and take the test in different test rooms according to their time slots.
On May 23, the district education examination and enrollment center published the list of students who passed the assessment online, and students can check the assessment results online.
