Bosnia and Herzegovina Olympic Committee President: Firmly believes China has the ability to successfully host the Winter Olympics during this special period - Xinhua News Agency
Sarajevo, December 11 (Xinhua) -- Bosnian Olympic Committee President Ivan Kvešić recently stated that Bosnia and Herzegovina is eagerly anticipating the Beijing Winter Olympics and firmly believes that China has the capability to successfully host the Games during this special period.
Recently, Ji Ping, the Chinese Ambassador to Bosnia and Herzegovina, met with Kvešić, the President of the Olympic Committee of Bosnia and Herzegovina, at the Olympic Center in Sarajevo.
During the meeting, Kvešić spoke highly of the Bosnian-Chinese relations and said that he had visited China during the 2008 Beijing Summer Olympics and was deeply impressed by China's excellent organization. He firmly believed that China was capable of successfully hosting the Winter Olympics during this special period. Bosnia and Herzegovina is looking forward to the Beijing Winter Olympics, and the Bosnian Olympic Committee is actively organizing its participation. Bosnia and Herzegovina hopes to take this opportunity to carry out broader exchanges and cooperation with China in the field of sports.
Ji Ping stated that China and Poland share a special "Olympic bond".
The 1984 Sarajevo Winter Olympics were successfully held here, and in two months, the 2022 Beijing Winter Olympics will also open, presenting the world with a simple, safe and wonderful event.
We look forward to deepening exchanges and cooperation between the two countries in areas such as preparation for winter sports events and athlete training. The Chinese Embassy in Bosnia and Herzegovina is willing to continue to play a bridging role and take the Beijing Winter Olympics as an opportunity to promote the continuous deepening of cultural exchanges between the two countries, so that the people of both countries can "move towards the future together." We also wish the athletes from Bosnia and Herzegovina great success in Beijing.
Prior to the meeting, the Olympic Committee of Bosnia and Herzegovina held the "10th Annual Best Athlete" award ceremony, where Ji Ping, as a special guest, presented the award to the best young athlete in Bosnia and Herzegovina.
Promotional videos for the Beijing Winter Olympics were played on a loop at the event.
