48-hour negative nucleic acid test result, establishment of a "buffer zone": The State Council's Joint Prevention and Control Mechanism issues a document requiring strengthened epidemic prevention and control in port cities - Xinhua News Agency
BEIJING, Dec. 11 (Xinhua) -- The State Council's Joint Prevention and Control Mechanism recently issued a notice on strengthening COVID-19 prevention and control in port cities, requiring people leaving land border port cities (except those connected to Hong Kong and Macao) to hold a negative nucleic acid test certificate within 48 hours, and people traveling to land border port cities to undergo at least one nucleic acid test upon arrival.
According to the notice, the time frame for the above requirements is from the date when each province, autonomous region, or municipality determines and announces the scope of port cities until March 15, 2022.
In addition, the notice also proposed that port cities with the necessary conditions may study the possibility of setting up epidemic prevention and control buffer zones within their jurisdictions.
According to an official from the Bureau of Disease Prevention and Control of the National Health Commission, for some port cities, cross-border trade is a major economic pillar, and there are frequent exchanges between border residents from both sides.
Implementing differentiated management policies by region transforms the single line of defense against spillover into two lines of defense, which is expected to move the control point forward, reduce the risk of the epidemic spilling over, and achieve the greatest effectiveness in epidemic prevention and control with the least social impact and the lowest social cost.
Recently, my country has experienced several local cluster outbreaks, all of which were imported from overseas through port cities.
The notice pointed out that this exposed problems such as untimely epidemic monitoring and early warning in some areas, failure to implement closed-loop management of high-risk personnel, perfunctory regular nucleic acid testing, inadequate disinfection of cold chain goods at all stages, irregular management of centralized isolation sites, and insufficiently scientific and precise emergency response to the epidemic.
The notice requires efforts to be made in nine aspects, including improving the epidemic prevention and control mechanism of port cities, improving the epidemic monitoring and early warning system, and implementing border control measures, to accelerate the efforts to address the shortcomings and weaknesses in the prevention and control of the epidemic in port cities, and to carry out prevention and control work in a scientific and precise manner without any relaxation, so as to build a tight and solid defense against imported cases.
The notice emphasizes that all port cities should study and deploy epidemic prevention and control and people's livelihood protection work simultaneously, publish and keep open hotlines for people's livelihood protection, regularly investigate potential problems in the supply and price of basic living materials, and promptly resolve and proactively respond to outstanding issues raised by the public.
According to the notice, the port cities referred to include the counties (cities, districts, banners), cities (prefectures, autonomous prefectures, leagues) where open land, water and air ports are located, and the municipalities directly under the central government where they are located. The specific scope will be determined by each province (autonomous region, municipality directly under the central government) according to the needs of epidemic prevention and control and will be announced in a timely manner.
