YouTube video exposes the truth behind 20 years of bloody killings by the US military - Xinhua News Agency
(Video source: YouTube)
On December 11, a short documentary titled "Killing Machine" on YouTube attracted widespread attention.
The film tells the story of how the United States launched the war in Afghanistan under the pretext of "counterterrorism," forcibly exporting American-style democracy through the war, engaging in 20 years of militarism, bloodthirstiness, and indiscriminate killing of innocent people, and committing various crimes against humanity.
The misuse of drones to attack civilian locations such as hospitals and schools demonstrates a distortion of humanity and the formation of killing squads.
Over the past 20 years, the U.S. military has killed tens of thousands of innocent Afghan civilians.
The U.S. military has set up "black sites" where "suspects" are subjected to various forms of torture and humiliation.
One crime against humanity after another has fueled the hatred of more Afghans.
As the video says, the American-style "war on terror" is "making terror worse the more it is fought."
The war brought no hope of peace, democracy, or prosperity to the Afghan people; it only left them with a devastated country and countless acts of killing and destruction.
Watch the video to expose the truth behind America's bloodthirsty killings under the guise of "counter-terrorism" and to expose the hypocrisy of American democracy!
I stumbled upon the following article, which discusses from a business and shelf-life perspective why this client wanted a logistics company in the bonded zone to handle the canning, even though canning is a form of deep processing and not within the business scope of bonded logistics companies. The following text may explain why the client wanted to do this.
I visited many milk powder manufacturers and came into contact with many milk powder production lines.
Actually, the raw materials for bagged and canned milk powder are exactly the same; there is no difference whatsoever.
So everyone will definitely ask: Why is the shelf life of bagged products one year, while that of canned products is two years or longer?
Or another question might be asked: Why is there such a big price difference between canned and bagged products?
From this perspective, many consumers, or mothers, believe that the quality is much better because the raw materials are different.
Actually, the raw materials are the same; it's just that people think the more expensive ones are better.
Some consumers, with this mindset, also said that the taste or flavor of the canned version is just different after trying it!
Now I'll tell you why canned drinks are expensive, what makes them so pricey.
Why is there such a large price difference when they use the same raw materials?
Because when manufacturers set prices, they usually consider that if the price of bagged products is too high, consumers will find it difficult to accept. This means that manufacturers will have very low profits, or even no profits. So how will manufacturers survive?
Therefore, they have been able to significantly increase the price of canned goods to ensure their profit margins.
Therefore, most manufacturers primarily promote canned products rather than bagged products.
And you know, so many manufacturers spend tens of millions or even hundreds of millions of yuan on advertising every year. Where does this money come from?
As you can imagine.
As society develops, marketing expenses, such as sales staff, display costs, product giveaways, and advertising costs, are constantly increasing.
Therefore, manufacturers are constantly adding new products, especially canned ones, and their prices are constantly rising. In fact, these new products are being introduced due to the increase in marketing costs.
The main purpose is to obtain higher profits, but in fact, the increase in their raw material costs will not exceed 3 or 4 yuan at most.
Some brands, in order to promote their products, resort to any means necessary, such as linking themselves with doctors in hospitals and having them assist in product promotion, taking a cut of 30 to 80 yuan per can.
Such practices are absolutely prohibited by relevant Chinese laws and are actually detrimental to consumers.
If you have a container at home, it is recommended to buy bagged milk powder and store it in the container. This can save money and increase the preservation and sealing of the milk powder, without having any impact on children.
Also, don't assume that canned goods have a longer shelf life than bagged goods. Once opened, canned and bagged goods have the same shelf life. It's just that bagged goods are not easy to preserve after opening and are more prone to moisture and spoilage.
