The stock of naked carp in Qinghai Lake increased by 7,100 tons this year - Xinhua News Agency
Xining, December 11 (Xinhua) -- According to the latest monitoring results from the Qinghai Provincial Department of Agriculture and Rural Affairs, the stock of naked carp in Qinghai Lake has increased by 7,100 tons this year compared to last year, reaching 108,500 tons, representing a cumulative increase of more than 40 times compared to the initial stage of conservation in 2002.
The Qinghai Lake naked carp, also known as "Huangyu," is a precious fish species unique to Qinghai Lake. It plays a crucial role in maintaining the safety of the "water-fish-bird" ecological chain and biodiversity in the Qinghai Lake basin.
In the 1960s and 70s, the number of naked carp in Qinghai Lake decreased sharply due to factors such as large-scale hunting by humans and the increasing degradation of the breeding water environment. In 2002, the stock of naked carp in Qinghai Lake was only 2,592 tons.
In 2004, the Qinghai Lake naked carp was listed as an endangered species in the China Species Red List.
Since 2003, Qinghai Province has implemented a lake closure for fish breeding, prohibiting any unit, collective or individual from fishing for naked carp in Qinghai Lake and its main rivers and tributaries, and prohibiting the sale of naked carp and its products.
Meanwhile, through measures such as artificial propagation and release, clearing the main rivers flowing into Qinghai Lake, and designing scientifically sound "fish passageways," the conservation efforts have been continuously strengthened, and the stock of naked carp in Qinghai Lake has increased year by year.
Yang Lin, deputy director of the Department of Agriculture and Rural Affairs of Qinghai Province, introduced that as of now, nearly 180 million naked carp have been artificially propagated and released into Qinghai Lake, contributing more than 23% to the recovery of naked carp resources in Qinghai Lake.
The Sanjiangyuan region in Qinghai is an important ecological barrier and water conservation area in my country and even Asia, while Qinghai Lake is a natural barrier and ecological functional area for controlling the eastward spread of desertification in the west.
In order to protect the ecological environment of the Sanjiangyuan region and Qinghai Lake, protect aquatic wildlife, and maintain the biodiversity of the Qinghai-Tibet Plateau, Qinghai has successively issued notices on banning fishing in key waters of the Yangtze River, the Yellow River, and Qinghai Lake this year, establishing a comprehensive management system for banning fishing in "one river, one lake, and one lake".
