Yunnan: Standardizing and Unifying the Management of Rural Public Service Positions - Xinhua News Agency
Kunming, December 12 (Xinhua) -- To continue providing employment assistance to those lifted out of poverty and to consolidate and expand the achievements in poverty alleviation, Yunnan Province recently issued relevant policies to promote the management of rural public service positions for rural revitalization, thus contributing to the comprehensive advancement of rural revitalization.
According to an official from the Yunnan Provincial Department of Human Resources and Social Security, Yunnan has created 448,300 rural public service jobs to provide employment for impoverished rural groups, including those lifted out of poverty. These jobs play a vital role in helping people escape poverty to increase their income through employment, consolidating the achievements of poverty alleviation, and effectively improving the capacity of various public services in rural areas.
The new regulations were jointly issued by seven departments in Yunnan Province, including the Human Resources and Social Security Bureau, the Rural Revitalization Bureau, and the Finance Bureau. They mainly standardize the scope of recruitment for rural public service positions, fund management, job development, and job management.
Regarding job development and setup, the new regulations clarify that job setup should be carried out in accordance with the principles of "setting up jobs as needed, assigning personnel based on jobs, dynamic management, and total quantity control," "whoever develops, uses, and is responsible for," and "one person, one job, voluntary disclosure, and unified management."
The recruitment process must follow the steps of announcement, application, review, public announcement, hiring, pre-job training, and job placement.
In addition, the new regulations clarify the specific responsibilities of the main departments responsible for developing rural public service positions, the subsidy standards and methods for rural public service positions, stipulate that each department responsible for developing rural public service positions should purchase commercial accident insurance for the personnel placed in rural public service positions, and require relevant departments to regularly supervise the distribution of subsidies for rural public service positions.
