Many people have ideals when they are young, but when they get old, they forget their ideals or pursue them but become obsessed.
They drift further and further away from their ideals, and the dragon-slaying hero eventually becomes the dragon himself.
I think "left and right" generally refers to constraint and freedom. China's inherent historical and cultural genes have led to China as a whole being leaning to the left.
In China, the right wing prioritizes freedom, efficiency, and development, while the left wing emphasizes oversight, fairness, and security.
Society as a whole now hopes to pay more attention to fairness. At the same time, with the competition between China and the United States, a left-leaning tendency is certain and is expected to continue for many years.
