Let's take a look at some [strange trending topics] today.
What constitutes normal public opinion?
Three trending topics were randomly selected: the Dragon Raises Its Head on the Second Day of the Second Lunar Month, Orion's price increase, and the Lalamove incident. The spread of public opinion formed a peak, and then the index declined (smooth curve) and eventually dissipated. If secondary public opinion occurred, a small camel hump would appear again.
They look almost identical to the "Online Public Opinion Evolution Model" that the Cyberspace Administration of China once displayed on its official website.
What constitutes abnormal public opinion?
Six trending topics from the same event were randomly selected and presented as [isolated peak], [jagged], and [cliff-like].
[Isolated Peak] refers to artificially inflated popularity, quickly climbing to the top of the trending topics list and attracting public attention; [Sawtooth] refers to periodic inflated popularity, ensuring the topic lingers on the trending topics list; [Cliff-like] refers to a collective withdrawal, where the trending topic has fulfilled its "function" and is now moving on to a new task or battlefield.
In Figure 9, the peak of the popularity of one event coincides with the trough of another event, with the timing being exactly the same. This must mean that a group of online trolls received the mission and launched a new offensive.
The professionalism of black PR is evident: dozens of trending topics appearing simultaneously, black market accounts meticulously plan which ones attract attention, which ones provide scientific information, which ones incite conflict and create momentum, which ones divert attention, which ones influence perception, which ones mislead judgment, which ones incite emotions, and which ones coerce decision-making. They take into account almost all elements of public opinion dissemination and spread.
Communication is a science. If we set aside all subjective factors such as stance and emotion and focus solely on objective data, even smear campaigns will have nowhere to hide.
Every step leaves a trace; let's dig out these traces together.
Data source: Hot Search Time Machine.
Mauritius and other countries report first cases of Omicron virus infection - Xinhua News Agency
Xinhua News Agency, Beijing, December 12 (Xinhua) -- According to reports from Xinhua correspondents abroad, Mauritius, Cyprus, and Malawi have recently reported their first cases of infection with the Omeprone strain of the novel coronavirus.
Mauritius reported its first two cases of Omeprone virus infection on the 10th.
According to Mauritian Health Minister Kellesh Jagutpal, one of the infected individuals was a tourist who arrived in Mauritius on November 27 from South Africa; the other infected individual was a Mauritian resident who tested positive for COVID-19 on November 30 after coming into contact with someone who had recently traveled to South Africa and returned.
After being isolated and treated at the hospital, both infected individuals tested negative for nucleic acid and have now returned to their respective residences.
On October 10, the Cypriot Ministry of Health announced the country's first three confirmed cases of infection with the Omeprone virus strain.
All three are students who returned from a trip abroad earlier this month. Since they all had mild symptoms, they were not hospitalized.
To prevent the spread of the Omeprone strain, the Serbian government has been continuously increasing its prevention and control efforts.
From December 6 to January 10 next year, passengers aged 12 and above arriving in Serbia by air will be required to undergo a nucleic acid test at the airport at their own expense.
The Serbian Ministry of Health also announced on the 10th that it will begin vaccinating children aged 5 to 11 in the country with the Pfizer COVID-19 vaccine.
Malawi's Health Minister Kumbize Chiponda said on the 9th that the country had discovered its first three cases of infection with the Omeprone virus strain.
The country's health authorities conducted genome sequencing on 12 COVID-19 positive samples collected between November 9 and December 2, which led to the discovery of these three cases of infection.
