From the past to the present, I have always opposed any form of slander and abuse, and I cannot accept such personal attacks.
In a civilized society, we can tolerate everything, but we must eliminate such villains.
If we disregard political parties and factions, what we should resist first is this kind of uncivilized behavior.
From the moment you started sending me a Facebook friend request, to your sarcastic posts, and then to your attempt to post what you claimed was my home address and my father's name on social media, I have remained silent.
After that, you went even further, not only tagging me six times a day, but also continuing to discuss some veiled and humiliating things about me with your so-called friends on Facebook, such as my appearance, figure, fertility, and comments about things like giving me hickeys in bed and asking if I should have sex with you. I... never mind.
To my surprise, I later received messages from several friends about a photo of me uploaded to your Facebook account along with sexually harassing comments.
I'm sorry, but as a girl, I can no longer remain silent.
After the news of my calling the police was uploaded, you didn't stop at all; instead, you became even more arrogant.
I don't care about your political background or your social status. In our society, respect between the sexes is essential.
Yes, you can continue with these sarcastic, veiled, humiliating, and abusive remarks. You can continue to say that you are just showing concern and care for me. You can continue to believe that this is not harassment. You can even continue to deny that you made the picture or continue to make all kinds of offensive remarks.
That's right, I can't, and I don't have the ability to, stop you.
I neither know you nor want to know you, and you have no right to judge my appearance or figure.
I don't even think any girl would willingly allow herself to be humiliated like this in exchange for fame.
My friend asked me, "Are you okay?"
Even if I say yes, you won't believe me.
I don't think any girl could say she's okay after being bullied like this.
Whether in the workplace, society, politics, or business, only those who lack even basic morality would choose to harm any woman in this way.
I believe that justice resides in the hearts of the people.
I've included some of the comments for everyone to judge.
Since you posted it yourself, no one can impersonate you, right?
All I can say is that you are an enemy of civilization.
