Vietnam People's Daily Online - Vietnamese Prime Minister Pham Minh Chinh attends the Third Vietnam National Digital Technology Enterprises Development Forum
Two main sessions were held during the Third Vietnam National Digital Technology Enterprises Development Forum, with discussions focusing on two main themes: digital technology enterprises and the country's digital transformation, and digital technology enterprises and economic recovery and development during and after the COVID-19 pandemic.
Minister of Information and Communications Nguyen Manh Hung stated that despite the ongoing COVID-19 pandemic in 2021, the number of digital technology companies in Vietnam and their operating revenue still maintained growth momentum, reaching nearly 10%.
In 2021, Vietnam cultivated a large number of typical digital products, focusing on solving major challenges facing Vietnam. Many digital products have gone global, and Vietnam's ranking in digital technology has improved.
Minister Nguyen Manh Hung called on digital technology companies to take responsibility for developing national digital transformation platforms, saying that undertaking the task of developing these national digital platforms is to fulfill the national mission.
At the forum, leaders of various ministries and state agencies, as well as enterprises, organizations and individuals researching, developing, applying and transferring digital technologies, shared their groundbreaking ideas and solutions for mobilizing and pooling resources across society to develop Vietnamese technology enterprises, jointly promote the country's digital transformation, and achieve post-pandemic economic recovery.
In his speech at the forum, Prime Minister Pham Minh Chinh emphasized that digital transformation is an inevitable path for the world and an objective requirement for development.
Digital transformation has become a global issue, and since it serves everyone, it requires the mobilization of the entire population to participate.
People and enterprises are the core, main body, goal and driving force of digital transformation.
Therefore, all policies must be for the benefit of the people and businesses.
Prime Minister Pham Minh Chinh emphasized that digital transformation must embody national spirit, rely primarily on internal strength as a strategic, long-term, and decisive factor, and use external forces as an important and breakthrough point.
He also believes that digital transformation needs to be driven to develop in depth and sustainably, participate in the prevention and control of COVID-19, economic recovery and development, respond to subsequent changes, overcome the depletion of natural resources, and help green transformation and the development of green energy.
Digital transformation requires participation in the establishment of databases to protect and promote national cultural values, historical traditions, and local customs, and to promote digital transformation in areas such as banking, taxation, land management and development databases, and logistics.
The ultimate goal of digital transformation is to make people happier and the country more prosperous and developed.
Prime Minister Pham Minh Chinh urged governments at all levels, agencies, and businesses to strengthen leadership and guidance in the development of digital technologies, raise awareness of digital transformation, continue to develop and improve systems for digital transformation, strengthen national governance, and promote the development of digital technology companies in a spirit of respect, communication, listening, positivity, and initiative.
During the forum, Prime Minister Pham Minh Chinh attended the award ceremony for the 2021 “Made in Vietnam” Excellent Digital Products Award and the opening ceremony of the “Made in Vietnam” Digital Products Exhibition.
