The "Wisdom Gathering in Hunan" 2021 China International Rail Transit and Equipment Manufacturing Industry Talent Summit Opens - Rolling News - Hunan Daily Website - Huasheng Online
Hunan Daily, December 10 (Reporter Zhou Zhiheng) – The “Wisdom of Hunan” 2021 China International Rail Transit and Equipment Manufacturing Industry Talent Summit opened in Zhuzhou on the 9th.
Wang Cheng, member of the Standing Committee of the Provincial Party Committee and Minister of the Organization Department of the Provincial Party Committee, attended the launching ceremony and delivered a speech.
Wang Cheng pointed out that holding the talent summit is an important measure to implement the spirit of the Central Talent Work Conference and the 12th Provincial Party Congress, demonstrating Hunan's sincerity in valuing, seeking, and making good use of talent.
Hunan has a fine tradition of recognizing, valuing, and respecting talent, a broad platform to support talent development, and favorable environmental conditions for achieving a better life. In recent years, it has deeply implemented the talent-led development strategy, taking the Furong Talent Action Plan as its guide, and has built a full-chain talent work pattern of attracting, cultivating, retaining, and utilizing talent, becoming a fertile ground for talent growth and achievement, a hotbed for innovation and entrepreneurship, and a happy land for living and working.
Currently, Hunan is fully implementing the strategic positioning and mission of "high-quality development, high efficiency, high quality, high standards, and new industries." It will further open its doors to attract talents, introduce better policies, concentrate more resources, and create better conditions for talent innovation and entrepreneurship. It looks forward to outstanding talents from all walks of life joining hands to pool their wisdom and strength for Hunan's high-quality development.
The event featured pavilions from Changsha, Zhuzhou, Xiangtan, and the Hunan Free Trade Zone. The Hunan Provincial Department of Science and Technology, the Hunan Provincial Department of Industry and Information Technology, and the Hunan Provincial Department of Human Resources and Social Security released a list of key technological innovation needs for advanced manufacturing-related industries, a talent demand catalog for the intelligent manufacturing industry, and a catalog of young talent needs for postdoctoral research stations in the intelligent manufacturing industry.
Forty-eight large enterprises, including CRRC, Zoomlion, and Broad Group, recruited talents on-site, with nearly a thousand recent graduates and professionals from relevant fields participating in talent matchmaking.
