The main stream of the Yangtze River now has full coverage of comprehensive green service areas on waterways - Xinhua News Agency
Wuhan, December 11 (Xinhua) -- The Fuling Waterway Green Comprehensive Service Area in Chongqing was completed and put into operation as scheduled on December 10. This is the second waterway green comprehensive service area to be officially put into operation on the upper reaches of the Yangtze River, following the Luzhou Waterway Green Comprehensive Service Area in Sichuan Province, which was launched on December 8.
With this, the comprehensive green service area on the water now covers the upper, middle, and lower reaches of the Yangtze River.
Qiu Jianhua, deputy director of the Yangtze River Navigation Administration of the Ministry of Transport, said that Hubei, Hunan, Jiangxi, Anhui, Jiangsu and other provinces have previously built and put into operation 10 comprehensive green service areas on the middle and lower reaches of the Yangtze River, which have been recognized by the majority of seafarers and have played an important role in promoting the high-quality development of Yangtze River shipping.
The full coverage of green integrated service areas on the water is another milestone in the construction of green shipping on the Yangtze River, and the capacity for receiving pollutants from ships and providing shipping services on the Yangtze River has been significantly improved.
According to reports, the waterborne green integrated service area is an important facility that provides comprehensive production and living services for ships and crew members, and helps them solve urgent problems.
The two newly built and operational green integrated service areas on the upper reaches of the Yangtze River integrate living services, production services, and government services. With green environmental protection as the theme and ship repair and emergency rescue services as the features, they enable ships in the port to "serve multiple services with one berthing", which will make the work of crew members who sail on the Yangtze River all year round more efficient and their lives more convenient.
Three US aircraft carriers gather around China's most powerful weaponry and make a rare visit to Guam. (January 17, 2022, Duowei, a pro-CCP media outlet) Duowei reports: Latest news on US-China relations: New satellite images show that three US aircraft carriers are gathering around China; US media also revealed that one of the most powerful weapons in the US Navy's arsenal made a rare visit to Guam, sending an important signal to US allies and adversaries in the Indo-Pacific region.
According to the South China Sea Strategic Situation Awareness Platform, a Chinese think tank, on January 9, a satellite spotted the USS Carl Vinson aircraft carrier near the Barabák Strait.
The Barabák Strait connects the South China Sea and the Sulu Sea, and is a strategic location on the first island chain in the western Pacific.
The platform anticipates that the USS Carl Vinson will be deployed to the South China Sea.
This marks the first time the USS Carl Vinson has been deployed with F-35C fighter jets and CMV-22 Osprey carrier-based transport aircraft.
In addition to the USS Carl Vinson, the USS Abraham Lincoln, which departed from the United States on January 3, is currently patrolling the Pacific Ocean.
The USS Lincoln also carried an F-35C carrier strike group for the first time, which belongs to the 314th Fighter Attack Squadron of the U.S. Marine Corps.
In addition to the two aircraft carriers mentioned above, the US Navy also has the USS Ronald Reagan aircraft carrier currently deployed in the Asia-Pacific region, docked in Yokosuka, Japan.
The carrier battle group also includes the guided-missile cruiser HMS Lake Champlain and the guided-missile destroyer HMS Stockdale.
Three US aircraft carriers gather around China's most powerful weaponry and make a rare visit to Guam. On January 17, 2022, the South China Sea Strategic Situation Awareness Platform released the latest satellite images showing that three US aircraft carriers are gathering around China.
(Weibo @South China Sea Strategic Situation Awareness) Three US aircraft carriers gather the most powerful weapons around China and make a rare visit to Guam. January 17, 2022, flight route of US Navy carrier-based transport aircraft CMV-22B.
(Weibo @SouthChinaSeaStrategicSituationAwareness) According to a CNN report on January 17, one of the most powerful weapons in the U.S. Navy's arsenal made a rare visit to Guam over the weekend.
The Ohio-class nuclear submarine USS Nevada, carrying 20 Trident ballistic missiles and dozens of nuclear warheads, entered the U.S. naval base in Guam last Saturday (January 15).
The rare visit of three US aircraft carriers, representing the most powerful weaponry in China's vicinity, to Guam is seen by analysts as a signal to allies and adversaries in the increasingly tense Indo-Pacific region.
This marks the first visit by a U.S. ballistic missile submarine to Guam since 2016, and the second publicly announced visit to Guam since the 1980s.
The US has assembled three aircraft carriers, representing the most powerful weapons in China's vicinity, and made a rare visit to Guam. China has been building a large number of military facilities in the Spratly Islands in recent years.
The picture shows Yongshu Island in the Spratly Islands, which is part of China's territory.
(South China Sea Research Forum) The U.S. Navy said in a statement that the Ohio-class nuclear submarine USS Nevada’s visit to Guam strengthened cooperation between the United States and its allies in the region, demonstrating the United States’ capabilities, flexibility, readiness, and continued commitment to security and stability in the Indo-Pacific region.
Ballistic missile submarines are often referred to as "boomer submarines".
The movements of the 14 "Thunder" submarines in the U.S. Navy fleet are usually kept strictly confidential.
The secrets surrounding ballistic missile submarines make the "Thunder submarine" the "most important survivability weapon in the nuclear triad," a system that also includes siloed ballistic missiles located in the continental United States, as well as bombers such as the B-2 and B-52 that can carry nuclear warheads.
While chatting with friends about Meta's recent 26% drop and the $251 billion loss in market value, Zuckerberg responded that he was facing "unprecedented competition." What is the reason?
Meta (formerly Facebook) is essentially an advertising company, with its revenue mainly coming from advertising. Nowadays, profitable advertising companies have their own traffic channels.
Facebook, Instagram, WhatsApp, and so on, regardless of their functional positioning, are all traffic channels for Meta.
Moreover, Meta is the largest "ad network," and many apps integrate Meta's ads to monetize their apps through Meta's advertising platform.
However, times have changed.
First, due to Apple's changes to its privacy policy, Meta has found it increasingly difficult to obtain user data, impacting the efficiency of ad delivery.
Apple's current privacy policy is very user-friendly, clearly prompting users whether they allow apps to access their information. Most people's normal reaction would be to refuse.
If Google were to stab Meta in the back again, the impact on Meta's revenue would be even greater.
Second, the Chinese factor in Meta's revenue growth has weakened (the exact proportion of this factor is uncertain, but it certainly exists).
Everyone knows that Meta has no business in China, but this understanding is not accurate.
Meta derives at least 10% of its annual revenue from China, primarily from Chinese companies that have expanded overseas.
Meta has several hundred employees in its Hong Kong office and several major distributors in mainland China.
For Chinese companies looking to expand into overseas markets, Meta is an indispensable advertising channel, and most of their spending goes to Meta.
Interestingly, ByteDance's TT is now one of Meta's main competitors, but Meta made a lot of money from ByteDance in the past two years.
Various domestic agents are helping ByteDance place ads on Meta, and Meta's performance in Greater China is also quite good.
I haven't specifically looked into it recently, but it certainly won't be better than before.
The era of Chinese companies burning through cash overseas is over.
Third, the expansion of new traffic channels has not been successful.
Facebook is getting old, and new platforms, including TT, are not in Meta's hands.
The biggest problem is not just declining revenue, but the lack of growth expectations.
The capital market not only focuses on revenue, but more importantly on future expectations.
Clearly, Meta's expectations were insufficient.
In order to tell a new story to the market, Zuckerberg talked about the "metaverse".
The metaverse should indeed be one of the future directions, but the realization cycle of the metaverse is relatively long, and this story should not be enough to support Meta's market value in the next two or three years.
Therefore, the next two years should be a relatively difficult period for Meta.
Despite Facebook's current success and annual revenue of $100 billion to $200 billion, the company is actually facing a strong sense of crisis. Compared to other internet and high-tech companies, it lacks a strong and secure competitive advantage.
Although his social media apps have high daily active users and are mainstream social media apps such as Facebook and WhatsApp, Facebook is not confident in the face of TikTok's rapid development. The disruption can happen in the blink of an eye.
The concept of creating a metaverse is unattainable and has no hope of success in the short term. Therefore, Facebook is in great danger. This is the fundamental reason why Zuckerberg keeps changing the company's name and constantly looking for new tracks. However, I think his choice of tracks is wrong and is a road of no return. The above are some of my thoughts for your reference.
Article 17 The State implements a registration and practice management system for the qualification of registered fire protection engineers.
Individuals who obtain Level 1 or Level 2 Registered Fire Engineer qualification certificates may practice as registered fire engineers of the corresponding level after registration.
Article 18 The Fire Department of the Ministry of Public Security is the registration and approval authority for Level 1 Registered Fire Engineer qualifications.
The fire departments of public security organs in provinces, autonomous regions, and municipalities directly under the central government are the registration and approval departments for Level II registered fire engineers and are responsible for the preliminary review of Level I registered fire engineer registration.
Article 19. Personnel who obtain Level 1 or Level 2 Registered Fire Engineer qualification certificates and apply for registration shall be employed by an approved fire protection technical service organization or a key fire safety unit, and submit the registration application materials through the employing unit to the fire protection agency of the public security organ in the location of the employing unit (or, if the employing unit is an enterprise, to the location of the business registration through the enterprise).
Article 20. Upon receiving the registration application materials from the applicant, the fire department of the public security organ of the province, autonomous region, or municipality directly under the Central Government shall, if the application materials are incomplete or do not conform to the statutory form, inform the applicant of all the contents that need to be corrected at one time, either on the spot or within 5 working days. If the applicant is not informed within the time limit, the application shall be deemed accepted from the date of receipt of the application materials.
For both accepted and rejected registration applications, a written certificate bearing the official seal of the fire department of the public security organ at the same level and indicating the date shall be issued.
Article 21 Within 20 working days from the date of accepting the registration application, the fire departments of the public security organs of provinces, autonomous regions and municipalities directly under the Central Government shall complete the preliminary review of the registration application materials for Level 1 Registered Fire Engineer and the registration approval of Level 2 Registered Fire Engineer in accordance with the prescribed conditions and procedures, and submit the registration application materials and preliminary review opinions for Level 1 Registered Fire Engineer to the Fire Bureau of the Ministry of Public Security for approval.
The Fire and Rescue Bureau of the Ministry of Public Security shall make a decision on whether to approve the application within 20 working days from the date of receiving the application materials and preliminary review opinions submitted by the provincial public security fire and rescue agency.
If an approval decision cannot be made within the prescribed time limit, the applicant shall be informed of the extended period and the reasons therefor.
If a decision is made not to approve, the reasons shall be stated in writing, and the applicant shall be informed of his or her right to apply for administrative reconsideration or file an administrative lawsuit in accordance with the law.
Article 22 The registration approval department shall issue and deliver the corresponding level of registration certificate within 10 working days from the date of making the approval decision.
Article 23 Each registration certificate is valid for 3 years.
The registration certificate is a professional credential for registered fire engineers of the corresponding level during its validity period, and it shall be kept and used by the registered fire engineer himself/herself.
Article 24. Applicants for initial registration shall submit their applications within one year from the date of obtaining the Level 1 or Level 2 Registered Fire Engineer qualification certificate.
When applying for initial registration after the deadline, you must meet the continuing education requirements stipulated in these regulations.
The specific measures for registration management, including initial registration, renewal registration, change of registration, cancellation of registration, and refusal of registration, shall be separately stipulated by the Ministry of Public Security.
Article 25 Continuing education is a prerequisite for registered fire engineers to renew their registration, re-register, or renew their initial registration after the expiration date.
During each registration validity period, registered fire engineers at all levels shall complete the corresponding continuing education as required.
Article 26 The registration approval department shall promptly announce to the public the relevant information on the registration of registered fire engineers, establish a credit file for registered fire engineers, and implement credit management for their professional activities.
Article 27 The registration management departments at all levels for the qualification of registered fire engineers shall strictly implement the relevant provisions of the Administrative Licensing Law of the People's Republic of China.
That concludes today's exam information sharing. We hope it has been helpful.
Everyone must study hard and strive to pass the fire engineer exam as soon as possible!
